name: Food Matters II
description: What is at stake in achieving ethical food production, access to nutritious and environmentally sustainable food, and global food security?  Building on integrated learning from any New One I course, this course engages more deeply with such questions, along with community-led alternatives to dominant food systems, animal rights, biotechnology, and health and wellness.
exclusions: INI, Munk, SMC, TRI, UC, VIC and WDW One; NEW101Y1/NEW102Y1/NEW103Y1/NEW104Y1
